@page "/privacy"
<SeoHead Title="Privacy" Description="The actual data boundary of the static-first LifeOS public Website." CanonicalPath="/privacy" />
<PageIntro Eyebrow="Privacy" Title="A plain-language boundary for the public Website." Summary="The Website beta is informational and static-first. It does not collect personal details, expose local LifeOS records or run behavioural tracking." />
<section class="page-shell section privacy-copy"><article><h2>What this Website does</h2><p>It publishes product information, documentation structure and approved development proof. Public proof uses fictional or sanitized records.</p></article><article><h2>Analytics, cookies and tracking</h2><p>The Website beta includes no analytics, non-essential cookies, advertising pixels, fingerprinting or cross-site tracking. There is no consent banner because there is nothing in this release that requires one.</p></article><article><h2>Accounts and profiles</h2><p>There is no account, login, portal or behavioural profile on the public Website.</p></article><article><h2>Early Access</h2><p>The Early Access form is disabled and preview-only. No name, email, audience type or reason is submitted, stored or retained. Collection will not begin until a real handling path and updated policy exist.</p></article><article><h2>Desktop and Companion records</h2><p>Private LifeOS Desktop and Mobile Companion records are not uploaded to or exposed by this public Website.</p></article><article><h2>External links</h2><p>External destinations such as GitHub operate under their own privacy and data-handling policies.</p></article><article><h2>Technical boundary</h2><p>The static publish output excludes secrets, private repository documents, client information, local endpoints and local LifeOS records. This page describes the implementation delivered; it does not make broader legal guarantees.</p></article><p class="updated">Last updated: @PublicContent.LastUpdated.ToString("d MMMM yyyy")</p></section>
